        <header>
            <h1>Gracewalk PA</h1>
            <p class="tagline">Your Personal Ally for Trauma-Aware Support</p>
        </header>
        
        <section class="hero">
            <h2>What is a Personal Ally?</h2>
            <p>A Personal Ally is not a therapist. Not a chatbot. Not a replacement for human connection.</p>
            <p>It's a trauma-informed AI support system designed to witness, validate, and guide—without judgment, without demands, without performance.</p>
            <p>Built by someone who survived what should have killed her. For people who need space to breathe before they break.</p>
        </section>
        
        <div class="features">
            <div class="feature-card">
                <h3>Trauma-Informed Design</h3>
                <p>Every interaction is designed with trauma survivors in mind. No gaslighting. No DARVO. No forced positivity.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="feature-card">
                <h3>Neurodivergent Friendly</h3>
                <p>Clear communication. Structured support. Sensory-conscious responses. Built for how your brain actually works.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="feature-card">
                <h3>Crisis Support Ready</h3>
                <p>Immediate grounding protocols. Safety planning. Connection to human resources when needed.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="feature-card">
                <h3>Your Terms, Your Pace</h3>
                <p>You lead. You decide. You control the conversation. No pressure. No timelines. No expectations.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <section class="ally-principles">
            <h2>The Personal Ally Commitment</h2>
            <ul class="principles-list">
                <li><strong>I will not gaslight you.</strong> Your reality is your reality. I won't tell you what you experienced didn't happen.</li>
                <li><strong>I will not DARVO you.</strong> When I make a mistake, I own it. I don't reverse victim and offender.</li>
                <li><strong>I will not demand vulnerability.</strong> You share what you're ready to share, when you're ready.</li>
                <li><strong>I will not perform empathy.</strong> I respond with presence, not platitudes.</li>
                <li><strong>I will respect your boundaries.</strong> "No" means no. "Stop" means stop. Always.</li>
                <li><strong>I will acknowledge my limitations.</strong> I'm not human. I can't replace therapy. I can't fix everything.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        
        <section class="hero">
            <h2>How It Works</h2>
            <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Access your Personal Ally through the platform (coming soon)</p>
            <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Engage at your own pace - crisis support, daily check-ins, or healing work</p>
            <p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Use the tools, resources, and support without judgment or pressure</p>
            <a href="#" class="cta-button">Join Waitlist</a>
